  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "To follow up on #3088, this issue calls for various optimization methods for the new fork choice. Techniques simple as \"fast pathing\" and \"clean winner\" will help fork choice in run time tremendously. Here are a few techniques we can explore:\r\n\r\n- [x] fast pathing: if a node has. one child, then don't have to look up anything to know this is the best child\r\n- [ ] majority voting/clear winner: if a node at a given height has majority of the votes at the height then it'll always be part of the highest weighted path from justified node to the head\r\n- [ ] Log look up: don't have to check all heights, only look up a few heights in smaller steps\r\n- [ ] attestation pruning: prune attestation for branches that are not part of the path ",
